juniPolicyMIB.name: juniPolicyMIB

revisions.description: Add support for ATM Cell Mode configuration.
Policy precedence enhancements. Route class policy feature support.
Added new forward rules data objects.
Added noPolicy to the policy attachment type TC. Extended the range for the Classifier Control List Element ID.
Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names.
Extended rate limit profile objects. Added traffic class rule objects. Obsoleted policy traffic shaped objects.
Added TCP flag and IP flag support objects. Replaced juniPolicyProfileTable with juniPolicyAttachProfileTable. Created new confomance groupings.

Added color rule objects. Added Local Input Policy ID and Local Input Stats Enable objects to the juniPolicyProfileTable. Replaced juniPolicyIfTable with juniPolicyIfAttachTable. Replaced juniPolicyIfStatsTable with juniPolicyIfAttachStatsTable.
Initial version of this MIB module.

juniPolicyRowStatus.name: juniPolicyRowStatus
juniPolicyRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy *** LIMITED ACCESS LIST CONFIGURATION LEVEL *** RowStatus createAndGo/destroy operations have the following special-purpose semantics: createAndGo Create an entry having the specified configuration and append it to the target list, i.e. create a policy table entry with the associated policy name. destroy Destroy the specified list and all of its constituent elements. Policy row members may not be modified once the row has been created.

juniPolicyAdminState.name: juniPolicyAdminState
juniPolicyAdminState.description: This object is used to control the administrative state of a policy. Enabling a policy will result in the rules which make up a policy being applied to interfaces to which the policy is assigned. You should disable the admin state before adding/modifying any rules or classifier groups in this policy and then re-enable to apply the changes. This object may be modified while the row is active.

juniPolicyOperStatus.name: juniPolicyOperStatus
juniPolicyOperStatus.description: This obsolete object was used to retrieve the operational state of a policy. If a policy is disabled, it is not applied to any interfaces within the system. If a policy is invalid, there is a problem with the policy preventing it from being applied to an interface. An error code providing diagnostic information about the problem is found in juniPolicyErrorValue. If a policy is enabled, it has been applied to one or more interfaces within the system. This object was made obsolete due to some changes in E-Series which eliminated the possibility of a policy being operationaly disabled.

juniPolicyErrorValue.name: juniPolicyErrorValue

juniRateLimitExceededAction.name: juniRateLimitExceededAction
juniRateLimitExceededAction.description: Action to be taken when the access rate exceeds the bounds of the peak access rate.

juniRateLimitCommittedMarkVal.name: juniRateLimitCommittedMarkVal
juniRateLimitCommittedMarkVal.description: New IP precedence to be used when the juniRateLimitCommittedAction mark action is applied.

juniRateLimitConformedMarkVal.name: juniRateLimitConformedMarkVal
juniRateLimitConformedMarkVal.description: New IP prececence to be used when the juniRateLimitExceedCommittedAction mark action is applied.

juniRateLimitExceededMarkVal.name: juniRateLimitExceededMarkVal
juniRateLimitExceededMarkVal.description: New IP precedence to be used when the juniRateLimitExceedPeakAction mark action is applied.

juniRateLimitMask.name: juniRateLimitMask
juniRateLimitMask.description: Mask to be applied when executing a mark action.

juniRateLimitProfileType.name: juniRateLimitProfileType
juniRateLimitProfileType.description: The rate limit profile type (i.e. one-rate or two-rate). Defaults to two-rate, if not specified.

juniRateLimitExcessBurst.name: juniRateLimitExcessBurst
juniRateLimitExcessBurst.description: The excess committed access rate burst value in bytes. To be configured only if rate limit profile type is one-rate.

juniTrafficShapeProfileNextIndex.name: juniTrafficShapeProfileNextIndex
juniTrafficShapeProfileNextIndex.description: Obsolete scalar object returns the index of the next available row in the juniTrafficShapeProfileTable. This object returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that index allocation is unintended. This object became obsolete when the policy shaper capability was moved into the quality of service component.

juniTrafficShapeProfileTable.name: juniTrafficShapeProfileTable
juniTrafficShapeProfileTable.description: This table contains entries for elements of Traffic Shape Profile definitions. This table became obsolete when the policy shaper capability was moved into the quality of service component.

juniTrafficShapeProfileEntry.name: juniTrafficShapeProfileEntry
juniTrafficShapeProfileEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of a traffic shape profile element.

juniTrafficShapeProfileId.name: juniTrafficShapeProfileId
juniTrafficShapeProfileId.description: The number of the traffic shape profile entry which is defined by this row.

juniTrafficShapeProfileRowStatus.name: juniTrafficShapeProfileRowStatus
juniTrafficShapeProfileRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of conceptual rows within this table. All rowStatus modes are supported. To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniTrafficShapeProfileRowStatus

juniTrafficShapeProfileName.name: juniTrafficShapeProfileName
juniTrafficShapeProfileName.description: Specifies the name of the traffic shape profile defined by this row.

juniTrafficShapeReferenceCount.name: juniTrafficShapeReferenceCount
juniTrafficShapeReferenceCount.description: This object reflects the number of times a traffic shape profile object is referenced by policies.

juniTrafficShapeRate.name: juniTrafficShapeRate
juniTrafficShapeRate.description: The traffic shape rate in bits per second.

juniTrafficShapeBurst.name: juniTrafficShapeBurst
juniTrafficShapeBurst.description: The traffic shape burst in bytes.

juniClassifierControlListNextIndex.name: juniClassifierControlListNextIndex
juniClassifierControlListNextIndex.description: This scalar object returns the index of the next available row in the juniClassifierControlListTable. This object returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that index allocation is unintended.

juniClassifierControlListTable.name: juniClassifierControlListTable
juniClassifierControlListTable.description: This table contains entries for elements of classifier control lists. The details pertinent to each CLACL are found in the juniClassifierControlDefTable.

juniClassifierControlListEntry.name: juniClassifierControlListEntry
juniClassifierControlListEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an IP access list element.

juniClassifierControlListId.name: juniClassifierControlListId
juniClassifierControlListId.description: The number of the classifier control list to which this entry belongs.

juniClassifierControlListRowStatus.name: juniClassifierControlListRowStatus
juniClassifierControlListRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of conceptual rows within this table. Modes supported are create-and-go and destroy. To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: juniClassifierControlListRowStatus juniClassifierControlListElemId

juniClassifierControlListName.name: juniClassifierControlListName
juniClassifierControlListName.description: The name of the CLACL being defined.

juniClassifierControlListReferenceCount.name: juniClassifierControlListReferenceCount
juniClassifierControlListReferenceCount.description: Number of times this CLACL is referenced by policies.

juniClassifierControlListNextElementInde.name: juniClassifierControlListNextElementIndex
juniClassifierControlListNextElementInde.description: Each get of this object will return a unique index which may be used to create classifier control list elements. This object returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that index allocation is unintended.

juniClassifierControlListElementTable.name: juniClassifierControlListElementTable
juniClassifierControlListElementTable.description: This table contains entries for elements of classifier control lists. Entries belonging to the same control list are ordered, and comparisons to those entries are performed in that order until a match is detected. If no match is found, the default action is to 'deny'.

juniClassifierControlListElementEntry.name: juniClassifierControlListElementEntry
juniClassifierControlListElementEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an IP access list element.

juniClassifierControlListElemId.name: juniClassifierControlListElemId
juniClassifierControlListElemId.description: The relative position of this entry within its classifier control list. Classifier control list entries are searched in this sequence (low to high values) until a match is found.

juniClassifierControlListElemRowStatus.name: juniClassifierControlListElemRowStatus
juniClassifierControlListElemRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of conceptual rows within this table. This table provides a partial implementation for rowStatus. Rows may be created using createAndGo and createAndWait. Once a row has been made active the row status may not be changed.

juniClassifierControlListNotSrc.name: juniClassifierControlListNotSrc
juniClassifierControlListNotSrc.description: Invert the meaning of the source IP address and mask objects. For example 'not 10.10.0.90/255.255.255.255 (host address)' would result in all source addresses except for host 10.19.9.90 being matched.

juniClassifierControlListSrc.name: juniClassifierControlListSrc
juniClassifierControlListSrc.description: A source IP address. A subject IP address is first masked with the value of juniClassifierControlListSrcMask, then the result is compared to this value. Setting both this object and its corresponding mask to 0.0.0.0 acts as a wildcard, matching any source IP address.

juniClassifierControlListSrcMask.name: juniClassifierControlListSrcMask
juniClassifierControlListSrcMask.description: The IP address mask to be applied to a subject source IP address before comparing it to juniClassifierControlListSrc. Ones in the mask identify which bits in the subject IP address are significant for the comparison. To be considered valid, a nonzero value for this object must contain a single contiguous string of ones, beginning with the most significant bit of the mask.

juniClassifierControlListNotDst.name: juniClassifierControlListNotDst
juniClassifierControlListNotDst.description: Invert the meaning of the destination IP address and mask objects. For example, 'not 10.10.0.90/255.255.255.255 (host address)' would result in all source addresses except for host 10.19.9.90 being matched.

juniClassifierControlListDst.name: juniClassifierControlListDst
juniClassifierControlListDst.description: A destination IP address. A subject IP address is first masked with the value of juniClassifierControlListDstMask, then the result is compared to this value. Setting both this object and its corresponding mask to 0.0.0.0 acts as a wildcard, matching any destination IP address.

juniClassifierControlListDstMask.name: juniClassifierControlListDstMask
juniClassifierControlListDstMask.description: The IP address mask to be applied to a subject destination IP address before comparing it to juniClassifierControlListDst. Ones in the mask identify which bits in the IP address are significant for the comparison. To be considered valid, a nonzero value for this object must contain a single contiguous string of ones, beginning with the most significant bit of the mask.

juniClassifierControlListNotProtocol.name: juniClassifierControlListNotProtocol
juniClassifierControlListNotProtocol.description: Invert the meaning of the protocol object. For example, 'not TCP' matches any protocol except for TCP.

juniClassifierControlListProtocol.name: juniClassifierControlListProtocol
juniClassifierControlListProtocol.description: An IP Protocol value. Nonzero values match a specific IP Protocol value (e.g. 6 for TCP) carried in an IP packet; a value of zero acts as a wildcard, matching any IP Protocol.

juniClassifierControlListTosByte.name: juniClassifierControlListTosByte
juniClassifierControlListTosByte.description: The IP TOS byte value to match.

juniClassifierControlListMask.name: juniClassifierControlListMask
juniClassifierControlListMask.description: The mask to use for TOS byte checks. Allowed values are 0, 224, 252, 255.

juniClassifierControlListSrcOperator.name: juniClassifierControlListSrcOperator
juniClassifierControlListSrcOperator.description: Operator for use in comparing source ports.

juniClassifierControlListSrcFromPort.name: juniClassifierControlListSrcFromPort
juniClassifierControlListSrcFromPort.description: Source UDP or TCP 'from' port number.

juniClassifierControlListSrcToPort.name: juniClassifierControlListSrcToPort
juniClassifierControlListSrcToPort.description: Source UDP or TCP 'to' port number.

juniClassifierControlListDestOperator.name: juniClassifierControlListDestOperator
juniClassifierControlListDestOperator.description: Operator for use in comparing Destination ports.

juniClassifierControlListDestFromPort.name: juniClassifierControlListDestFromPort
juniClassifierControlListDestFromPort.description: Destination UDP or TCP 'from' port number.

juniClassifierControlListDestToPort.name: juniClassifierControlListDestToPort
juniClassifierControlListDestToPort.description: Destination UDP or TCP 'to' port number.

juniClassifierControlListICMPType.name: juniClassifierControlListICMPType
juniClassifierControlListICMPType.description: Optional ICMP message type for classification.

juniClassifierControlListICMPCode.name: juniClassifierControlListICMPCode
juniClassifierControlListICMPCode.description: Optional ICMP message code for classification.

juniClassifierControlListIGMPType.name: juniClassifierControlListIGMPType
juniClassifierControlListIGMPType.description: Optional IGMP message type for classification.

juniClassifierControlListTcpFlagsValue.name: juniClassifierControlListTcpFlagsValue
juniClassifierControlListTcpFlagsValue.description: Optional TCP flags value for classification.

juniClassifierControlListTcpFlagsMask.name: juniClassifierControlListTcpFlagsMask
juniClassifierControlListTcpFlagsMask.description: Optional TCP flags mask for classification. TCP flag bits not specified in the mask are don't care bits.

juniClassifierControlListIpFlagsValue.name: juniClassifierControlListIpFlagsValue
juniClassifierControlListIpFlagsValue.description: Optional IP flags value for classification.

juniClassifierControlListIpFlagsMask.name: juniClassifierControlListIpFlagsMask
juniClassifierControlListIpFlagsMask.description: Optional IP flags mask for classification. IP flag bits not specified in the mask are don't care bits

juniClassifierControlListIpFragValue.name: juniClassifierControlListIpFragValue
juniClassifierControlListIpFragValue.description: Optional IP flags mask for classification. IP flag bits not specified in the mask are don't care bits

juniClassifierControlListLocal.name: juniClassifierControlListLocal
juniClassifierControlListLocal.description: Match IP packets that are locally destined, i.e., destined to any one of router's interfaces.

juniClassifierControlListLocalPresent.name: juniClassifierControlListLocalPresent
juniClassifierControlListLocalPresent.description: Set to true if local classification field is configured.

juniClassifierControlListSaRouteClass.name: juniClassifierControlListSaRouteClass
juniClassifierControlListSaRouteClass.description: Match packets with source address route class matching this route class. The route class value of a packet can be determined in the secondary input policy attachment stage only. The route class value of a packet is assigned the value 0 in the input and output policy attachment stages.

juniClassifierControlListSaRouteClassPre.name: juniClassifierControlListSaRouteClassPresent
juniClassifierControlListSaRouteClassPre.description: Set to true if SA route class classification field is configured.

juniClassifierControlListDaRouteClass.name: juniClassifierControlListDaRouteClass
juniClassifierControlListDaRouteClass.description: Match packets with destination address route class matching this route class. The route class value of a packet can be determined in the secondary input policy attachment stage only. The route class value of a packet is assigned the value 0 in the input and output policy attachment stages.

juniClassifierControlListDaRouteClassPre.name: juniClassifierControlListDaRouteClassPresent
juniClassifierControlListDaRouteClassPre.description: Set to true if DA route class classification field is configured.

juniPolicyIfTable.name: juniPolicyIfTable
juniPolicyIfTable.description: This obsolete table contains entries which represent attachment of policies to interfaces. This table became obsolete when the juniPolicyIfAttTable was added.

juniPolicyIfEntry.name: juniPolicyIfEntry
juniPolicyIfEntry.description: Each entry contains the attachment of policy(s) to an interface.

juniPolicyIfInterfaceId.name: juniPolicyIfInterfaceId
juniPolicyIfInterfaceId.description: The interface number representing the interface to which policy(s) have been attached.

juniPolicyIfRowStatus.name: juniPolicyIfRowStatus
juniPolicyIfRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy *** LIMITED ACCESS LIST CONFIGURATION LEVEL *** RowStatus createAndGo/destroy operations have the following special-purpose semantics: createAndGo Create an entry having the specified configuration and append it to the target list, i.e. create a policy table entry with the associated policy name. destroy Destroy the specified list and all of its constituent elements. Policy row members may not be modified once the row has been created.

juniPolicyIfInputPolicyId.name: juniPolicyIfInputPolicyId
juniPolicyIfInputPolicyId.description: This object is used to control the attachment of input policies to the interface specified by juniPolicyIfInterfaceId, juniPolicyIfForwardingType and juniPolicyIfPolicyType. Attach a policy by setting this value to the ID of the policy. Remove a policy attachment by setting this value to zero. This object may be modified while the row is active. If so, the attachment is immediate.

juniPolicyIfOutputPolicyId.name: juniPolicyIfOutputPolicyId
juniPolicyIfOutputPolicyId.description: This object is used to control the attachment of output policies to the interface specified by juniPolicyIfInterfaceId, juniPolicyIfForwardingType and juniPolicyIfPolicyType. Attach a policy by setting this value to the ID of the policy. Remove a policy attachment by setting this value to zero. This object may be modified while the row is active. If so, the attachment is immediate.

juniPolicyIfInputStatsEnable.name: juniPolicyIfInputStatsEnable
juniPolicyIfInputStatsEnable.description: This object is used to control the enabling and disabling of statistics for an input policy attachment. Set this object to true to enable statistics. Set this object to false to disable statistics. This object may be modified while the row is active. The desired value must be set before the policy is attached or in a multiple object varbind. Failure to do so will result in the policy being attached with the previous value of juniPolicyInputStatsEnable.

juniPolicyIfOutputStatsEnable.name: juniPolicyIfOutputStatsEnable
juniPolicyIfOutputStatsEnable.description: This object is used to control the enabling and disabling of statistics for an output policy attachment. Set this object to true to enable statistics. Set this object to false to disable statistics. This object may be modified while the row is active. The desired value must be set before the policy is attached or in a multiple object varbind. Failure to do so will result in the policy being attached with the previous value of juniPolicyOutputStatsEnable.

juniPolicyIfAttachTable.name: juniPolicyIfAttachTable
juniPolicyIfAttachTable.description: This table contains entries which represent attachment of policies to interfaces.

juniPolicyIfAttachEntry.name: juniPolicyIfAttachEntry
juniPolicyIfAttachEntry.description: Each entry contains the attachment of policy(s) to an interface.

juniPolicyIfAttachInterfaceId.name: juniPolicyIfAttachInterfaceId
juniPolicyIfAttachInterfaceId.description: The interface number representing the interface to which policy(s) have been attached.

juniPolicyIfAttachForwardingType.name: juniPolicyIfAttachForwardingType
juniPolicyIfAttachForwardingType.description: The interface type (i.e. IP or CBF) which the policy have been attached to.

juniPolicyIfAttachPolicyType.name: juniPolicyIfAttachPolicyType
juniPolicyIfAttachPolicyType.description: The policy type (i.e. input, output or secondary input).

juniPolicyIfAttachRowStatus.name: juniPolicyIfAttachRowStatus
juniPolicyIfAttachRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy *** LIMITED ACCESS LIST CONFIGURATION LEVEL *** RowStatus createAndGo/destroy operations have the following special-purpose semantics: createAndGo Create an entry having the specified configuration and append it to the target list, i.e. create a policy table entry with the associated policy name. destroy Destroy the specified list and all of its constituent elements. Policy row members may not be modified once the row has been created.

juniPolicyIfAttachPolicyId.name: juniPolicyIfAttachPolicyId
juniPolicyIfAttachPolicyId.description: This object is used to control the attachment of policies to the interface specified by juniPolicyIfAttachInterfaceId, juniPolicyIfAttachForwardingType and juniPolicyIfAttachPolicyType. Attach a policy by setting this value to the ID of the policy. Remove a policy attachment by setting this value to zero. This object may be modified while the row is active. If so, the attachment is immediate.

juniPolicyIfAttachStatsEnable.name: juniPolicyIfAttachStatsEnable
juniPolicyIfAttachStatsEnable.description: This object is used to control the enabling and disabling of statistics for a policy attachment. Set this object to true to enable statistics. Set this object to false to disable statistics. This object may be modified while the row is active. The desired value must be set before the policy is attached or in a multiple object varbind. Failure to do so will result in the policy being attached with the previous value of juniPolicyIfAttachStatsEnable.

juniPolicyIfAttachStatsPreserve.name: juniPolicyIfAttachStatsPreserve
juniPolicyIfAttachStatsPreserve.description: This object is used to control the preserving of statistics when a policy is attached to an interface that already has a policy attachment. Set this object to true to preserve statistics. Get and GetNext will always return false. This object may be modified while the row is active. The desired value must be set before the policy is attached or in a multiple object varbind. Failure to do so will result in the policy being attached with the previous value of juniPolicyIfAttachStatsPreserve.

juniPolicyProfileTable.name: juniPolicyProfileTable
juniPolicyProfileTable.description: This obsolete table contains entries which represent attachment of policies to dynamic interfaces through profiles. This table became obsolete when the juniPolicyAttachProfileTable was added.

juniPolicyProfileEntry.name: juniPolicyProfileEntry
juniPolicyProfileEntry.description: Each entry contains the profile for attachment of policy(s) to a dynamic interface.

juniPolicyProfileId.name: juniPolicyProfileId
juniPolicyProfileId.description: The profile to which the policy attachment profile data belongs. When this profile is applied to a dynamic interface the associated policies will be applied to that interface.

juniPolicyProfileRowStatus.name: juniPolicyProfileRowStatus
juniPolicyProfileRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy *** LIMITED ACCESS LIST CONFIGURATION LEVEL *** RowStatus createAndGo/destroy operations have the following special-purpose semantics: createAndGo Create an entry having the specified configuration and append it to the target list, i.e. create a policy table entry with the associated policy name. destroy Destroy the specified list and all of its constituent elements. Policy row members may not be modified once the row has been created.

juniPolicyProfileInputPolicyId.name: juniPolicyProfileInputPolicyId
juniPolicyProfileInputPolicyId.description: This object is used to control the attachment of input policies to dynamic interfaces configured by the profile identified by juniPolicyProfileId. Attach a policy by setting this value to the ID of the policy. Remove a policy attachment by setting this value to zero. This object may be modified while the row is active. Changes made to a row in this table do not take effect until the profile is applied.

juniPolicyProfileOutputPolicyId.name: juniPolicyProfileOutputPolicyId
juniPolicyProfileOutputPolicyId.description: This object is used to control the attachment of output policies to dynamic interfaces configured by the profile identified by juniPolicyProfileId. Attach a policy by setting this value to the ID of the policy. Remove a policy attachment by setting this value to zero. This object may be modified while the row is active. Changes made to a row in this table do not take effect until the profile is applied to an interface.

juniPolicyProfileInputStatsEnable.name: juniPolicyProfileInputStatsEnable
juniPolicyProfileInputStatsEnable.description: This object is used to control the enabling and disabling of statistics for an input policy attachment performed by a profile. Set this object to true to enable statistics. Set this object to false to disable statistics. This object may be modified while the row is active. The changes will not take effect until the profile is applied to an interface.

juniPolicyProfileOutputStatsEnable.name: juniPolicyProfileOutputStatsEnable
juniPolicyProfileOutputStatsEnable.description: This object is used to control the enabling and disabling of statistics for an output policy attachment performed by a profile. Set this object to true to enable statistics. Set this object to false to disable statistics. This object may be modified while the row is active. The changes will not take effect until the profile is applied to an interface.

juniPolicyProfileLocalInputPolicyId.name: juniPolicyProfileLocalInputPolicyId
juniPolicyProfileLocalInputPolicyId.description: This object is used to control the attachment of local input policies to dynamic interfaces configured by the profile identified by juniPolicyProfileId. Attach a policy by setting this value to the ID of the policy. Remove a policy attachment by setting this value to zero. This object may be modified while the row is active. Changes made to a row in this table do not take effect until the profile is applied.

juniPolicyProfileLocalInputStatsEnable.name: juniPolicyProfileLocalInputStatsEnable
juniPolicyProfileLocalInputStatsEnable.description: This object is used to control the enabling and disabling of statistics for a local input policy attachment performed by a profile. Set this object to true to enable statistics. Set this object to false to disable statistics. This object may be modified while the row is active. The changes will not take effect until the profile is applied to an interface.

juniPolicyAttachProfileTable.name: juniPolicyAttachProfileTable
juniPolicyAttachProfileTable.description: This table contains entries which represent attachment of policies to dynamic interfaces through profiles.

juniPolicyAttachProfileEntry.name: juniPolicyAttachProfileEntry
juniPolicyAttachProfileEntry.description: Each entry contains the profile for attachment of policy(s) to a dynamic interface.

juniPolicyAttachProfileId.name: juniPolicyAttachProfileId
juniPolicyAttachProfileId.description: The profile to which the policy attachment profile data belongs. When this profile is applied to a dynamic interface the associated policies will be applied to that interface.

juniPolicyAttachProfileForwardingType.name: juniPolicyAttachProfileForwardingType
juniPolicyAttachProfileForwardingType.description: The interface type (i.e. IP or CBF) which the policy would be attached to.

juniPolicyAttachProfilePolicyType.name: juniPolicyAttachProfilePolicyType
juniPolicyAttachProfilePolicyType.description: The policy type (i.e. input, output or secondary input).

juniPolicyAttachProfileRowStatus.name: juniPolicyAttachProfileRowStatus
juniPolicyAttachProfileRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy *** LIMITED ACCESS LIST CONFIGURATION LEVEL *** RowStatus createAndGo/destroy operations have the following special-purpose semantics: createAndGo Create an entry having the specified configuration and append it to the target list, i.e. create a policy table entry with the associated policy name. destroy Destroy the specified list and all of its constituent elements. Policy row members may not be modified once the row has been created.

juniPolicyAttachProfilePolicyId.name: juniPolicyAttachProfilePolicyId
juniPolicyAttachProfilePolicyId.description: This object is used to control the attachment of policies to dynamic interfaces configured by the profile identified by juniPolicyAttachProfileId, juniPolicyAttachProfileForwardingType and juniPolicyAttachProfilePolicyType. Attach a policy by setting this value to the ID of the policy. Remove a policy attachment by setting this value to zero. This object may be modified while the row is active. Changes made to a row in this table do not take effect until the profile is applied.

juniPolicyAttachProfileStatsEnable.name: juniPolicyAttachProfileStatsEnable
juniPolicyAttachProfileStatsEnable.description: This object is used to control the enabling and disabling of statistics for an policy attachment performed by a profile. Set this object to true to enable statistics. Set this object to false to disable statistics. This object may be modified while the row is active. The changes will not take effect until the profile is applied to an interface.

juniPolicyIfStatsTable.name: juniPolicyIfStatsTable
juniPolicyIfStatsTable.description: Each entry within this obsolete table contains statistics data for an interface/policy rule combination. Interfaces with policies attached and statistics disabled are not represented in this table.

juniPolicyIfStatsEntry.name: juniPolicyIfStatsEntry
juniPolicyIfStatsEntry.description: Each entry defines a single statistics entry.

juniPolicyIfStatsIfId.name: juniPolicyIfStatsIfId
juniPolicyIfStatsIfId.description: The interface ID corresponding to the stats block represented by this row.

juniPolicyIfStatsPolicyType.name: juniPolicyIfStatsPolicyType
juniPolicyIfStatsPolicyType.description: The attachment point for the policy.

juniPolicyIfStatsPolicyId.name: juniPolicyIfStatsPolicyId
juniPolicyIfStatsPolicyId.description: The PolicyTable index of the policy corresponding to the stats block represented by this row.

juniPolicyIfStatsRulePrec.name: juniPolicyIfStatsRulePrec
juniPolicyIfStatsRulePrec.description: The precedence of the policy rule corresponding to the stats block represented by this row.

juniPolicyIfStatsRuleId.name: juniPolicyIfStatsRuleId
juniPolicyIfStatsRuleId.description: The index of the policy rule corresponding to the stats block represented by this row.

juniPolicyIfStatsClaclEntryNumber.name: juniPolicyIfStatsClaclEntryNumber
juniPolicyIfStatsClaclEntryNumber.description: The index of the clacl entry number corresponding to the stats block represented by this row.

juniPolicyIfStatsGreenPackets.name: juniPolicyIfStatsGreenPackets
juniPolicyIfStatsGreenPackets.description: The number of green packets policed by the policy rule.

juniPolicyIfStatsYellowPackets.name: juniPolicyIfStatsYellowPackets
juniPolicyIfStatsYellowPackets.description: The number of yellow packets policed by the policy rule.

juniPolicyIfStatsRedPackets.name: juniPolicyIfStatsRedPackets
juniPolicyIfStatsRedPackets.description: The number of red packets policed by the policy rule.

juniPolicyIfStatsGreenBytes.name: juniPolicyIfStatsGreenBytes
juniPolicyIfStatsGreenBytes.description: The number of green bytes policed by the policy rule.

juniPolicyIfStatsYellowBytes.name: juniPolicyIfStatsYellowBytes
juniPolicyIfStatsYellowBytes.description: The number of yellow bytes policed by the policy rule.

juniPolicyIfStatsRedBytes.name: juniPolicyIfStatsRedBytes
juniPolicyIfStatsRedBytes.description: The number of red bytes policed by the policy rule.

juniPolicyIfAttachStatsTable.description: Each entry within this obsolete table contains statistics data for an interface/policy rule combination. Interfaces with policies attached and statistics disabled are not represented in this table. This table became obsolete when policy precedence enhancements were made.

juniPolicyIfAttachStatsEntry.name: juniPolicyIfAttachStatsEntry
juniPolicyIfAttachStatsEntry.description: Each entry defines a single statistics entry.

juniPolicyIfAttachStatsIfId.name: juniPolicyIfAttachStatsIfId
juniPolicyIfAttachStatsIfId.description: The interface ID corresponding to the stats block represented by this row. This object became obsolete when policy precedence enhancements were made.

juniPolicyIfAttachStatsForwardingType.name: juniPolicyIfAttachStatsForwardingType
juniPolicyIfAttachStatsForwardingType.description: The forwarding type for the policy attachment. This object became obsolete when policy precedence enhancements were made.

juniPolicyIfAttachStatsPolicyType.name: juniPolicyIfAttachStatsPolicyType
juniPolicyIfAttachStatsPolicyType.description: The attachment point for the policy. This object became obsolete when policy precedence enhancements were made.

juniPolicyIfAttachStatsPolicyId.name: juniPolicyIfAttachStatsPolicyId
juniPolicyIfAttachStatsPolicyId.description: The PolicyTable index of the policy corresponding to the stats block represented by this row. This object became obsolete when policy precedence enhancements were made.

juniPolicyIfAttachStatsRulePrec.name: juniPolicyIfAttachStatsRulePrec
juniPolicyIfAttachStatsRulePrec.description: The precedence of the policy rule corresponding to the stats block represented by this row. This object became obsolete when policy precedence enhancements were made.

juniPolicyIfAttachStatsRuleId.name: juniPolicyIfAttachStatsRuleId
juniPolicyIfAttachStatsRuleId.description: The index of the policy rule corresponding to the stats block represented by this row. This object became obsolete when policy precedence enhancements were made.

juniPolicyIfAttachStatsClaclEntryNumber.name: juniPolicyIfAttachStatsClaclEntryNumber
juniPolicyIfAttachStatsClaclEntryNumber.description: The index of the clacl entry number corresponding to the stats block represented by this row. This object became obsolete when policy precedence enhancements were made.

juniPolicyIfAttachStatsGreenPackets.name: juniPolicyIfAttachStatsGreenPackets
juniPolicyIfAttachStatsGreenPackets.description: The number of green packets policed by the policy rule. This object became obsolete when policy precedence enhancements were made.
